# Accessibility and UI Rules

- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive controls.
- Provide visible focus styles and never remove focus outlines without replacement.
- Use semantic HTML and proper heading hierarchy in templates and admin pages.
- Ensure form controls have labels, help text where needed, and accessible error messages.
- Use ARIA only when semantic HTML cannot express intent.
- Validate color contrast and avoid relying on color alone for status feedback.
- Provide accessible loading, empty, error, and success states for async workflows.
- Ensure modals, notices, and toasts are announced appropriately to assistive tech.
